== Acute Epiglottitis
=== Etiology
*H. influenzae* type B (usually children).  
=== Clinical Feature
- Sudden high fever
- drooling
- muffled voice
- severe sore throat
- inspiratory stridor.  

*High-yield:* Avoid tongue depressor examination in suspected child—may trigger laryngospasm.
=== Treatment
- Maintain airway (intubation/tracheostomy if required)
- IV antibiotics (ceftriaxone)
- steroids
