= Esophagus
== Foreign Body Esophagus
=== Examples
Coins (children), meat bolus, dentures.  
=== Clinical Features
- Dysphagia
- salivation
- retrosternal pain
- vomiting
- respiratory distress (pressure on trachea). 
=== Treatment
Removal via rigid esophagoscopy under GA.
=== Complication during Esophagoscopy/ Removal
- *Perforation:* Neck emphysema, mediastinitis, fever, chest pain.  
- *Bleeding or FB slippage:* may lead to bronchial aspiration.
== Esophagal perforation
- *Small perforation:* NPO, IV antibiotics, feeding gastrostomy.  
- *Large:* Surgical repair, drainage of mediastinum.
== Carcinoma Esophagus
=== Clinical Features
- *Risk Factors:* Smoking, alcohol, reflux, achalasia, hot food.  
- Progressive dysphagia (solids → liquids)
- regurgitation
- weight loss
- aspiration cough.  
=== Investigation
- Barium swallow (irregular narrowing)
- endoscopy with biopsy
- CT chest for staging.  
=== Treatment
- Early: Esophagectomy ± gastric pull-up.  
- Palliative stenting or radiotherapy for advanced cases.
== Achalasia Cardia
=== Etiology
degeneration of nerves in the lower esophageal sphincter, leading to a failure to relax
=== Clinical Feature
- Dysphagia for solids + liquids
- Regurgitation
- Retrosternal fullness
- Weight loss.  
=== Treatment
- Balloon dilatation
- Heller's myotomy
- Botulinum toxin injection.
